<subSubSection pageId="0" pageNumber="159" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="159">Diagnosis.</paragraph>
<paragraph pageId="0" pageNumber="159">
This new taxon is very similar to typical 
<taxonomicName authority="Tourn. ex L." authorityName="Stapf" authorityYear="1915" baseAuthorityName="Reut." class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Phelypaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phelypaea boissieri" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">Phelypaea boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, and is compliant with morphometric characteristics in the description of the plant after 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.286" author="Reuter, G" journalOrPublisher="PhytoKeys" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" refId="B11" refString="Reuter, G, 1847. https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.286" url="https://doi.org/10.5962/bhl.title.286" year="1847">Reuter (1847</bibRefCitation>
: 42, sub 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" genus="Anoplanthus" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Anoplanthus biebersteinii subsp. var. var. boissieri" order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="variety" species="biebersteinii" subSpecies="var." variety="boissieri">Anoplanthus biebersteinii var. boissieri</taxonomicName>
), 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/4104573" author="Stapf, O" journalOrPublisher="Kew" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" pagination="285 - 295" refId="B13" refString="Stapf, O, 1915. The Genus Phelipaea. Bull. Misc. Inform. Kew 1915 (6): 285 - 295, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/4104573" title="The Genus Phelipaea. Bull. Misc. Inform." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/4104573" volume="1915" year="1915">Stapf (1915)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.2307/1220740" author="Nicolson, DH" journalOrPublisher="Taxon" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" pagination="651 - 657" refId="B6" refString="Nicolson, DH, 1975. Diphelypaea (Orobanchaceae), nom. nov. and other cauterizations on a nomenclatural hydra. Taxon 24 (5-6): 651 - 657, DOI: https://doi.org/10.2307/1220740" title="Diphelypaea (Orobanchaceae), nom. nov. and other cauterizations on a nomenclatural hydra." url="https://doi.org/10.2307/1220740" volume="24" year="1975">Nicolson (1975)</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation DOI="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-8748.2009.01673.x" author="Cullen, J" journalOrPublisher="Curtis's Botanical Magazine" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" pagination="379 - 388" refId="B3" refString="Cullen, J, 2010. Phelypaea boissieri: Orobanchaceae. Curtis's Botanical Magazine 26 (4): 379 - 388, DOI: https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-8748.2009.01673.x" title="Phelypaea boissieri: Orobanchaceae." url="https://doi.org/10.1111/j.1467-8748.2009.01673.x" volume="26" year="2010">Cullen (2010)</bibRefCitation>
but differs significantly in color and, usually, a higher stem. In typical 
<taxonomicName class="Magnoliopsida" family="Asteraceae" genus="P." kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="P. boissieri" order="Asterales" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="boissieri">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">P. boissieri</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, flowers are deeply red, and stem, calyx and scales are red to brown, or rarely pale-brown, whereas in the 
<taxonomicName authority="Tourn. ex L." authorityName="Ue. Subasi, R. Piwowarczyk, O. Sanchez Pedraja" authorityYear="2021" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Orobanchaceae" form="lutea" genus="Phelypaea" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Plantae" lsidName="Phelypaea boissieri subsp. f." order="Lamiales" pageId="0" pageNumber="159" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="form" species="boissieri" subSpecies="f.">Phelypaea boissieri f. lutea</taxonomicName>
corolla, calyx, and scales are yellow to orange with black folds in the corolla, with only the stem being brownish (Fig. 
<figureCitation captionStart="Figure 3" captionStartId="F3" captionText="Figure 3. Habitat and general habit of Phelypaea boissieri f. lutea at 2,470 m alt. in Cilo Mountains, Hakkari province, SE Turkey. Phot. Ue. Subasi." figureDoi="10.3897/phytokeys.186.77575.figure3" httpUri="https://binary.pensoft.net/fig/621091" pageId="0" pageNumber="159">3</figureCitation>
).
</paragraph>
